From Okungbowa Aiwerie, Asaba  A 40-year-old man has taken his life in Okpanam in Oshimili North Local Government Area of Delta State The deceased identified as Victor was found dangling from the ceiling fan in his bedsitter on Sunday. He did not leave a suicide note, except two phone numbers he scribbled on a piece of paper.  The deceased, The Nation gathered, who hailed from Calabar, Cross Rivers State, was an electrician. It was gathered that the deceased had a male child who lives with his mother. A source said that no one knew the time of his death, but a neighbour raised the alarm about 1.00p.m on the fateful day, adding that police evacuated his body about 7.00 p.m. Police spokesman DSP Onome Onowakpoyeya confirmed the incident.